Privacy Policy for Tabletop Tool

Last Updated: 03/01/2025

Thank you for using Tabletop Tool (the "App"). This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our App. Please read this policy carefully to understand our practices regarding your data.

1. No Data Collection
Tabletop Tool does not collect, store, or share any personal or sensitive user data. The App is designed to function entirely offline, and no information entered into the App is transmitted outside of your device.

2. Information You Provide
The App allows you to input data (e.g., health points, item tracking) for use in tabletop games. This information is stored locally on your device and is not accessible to us or any third parties. You are solely responsible for the data you input into the App.

3. No Third-Party Services
The App does not integrate with any third-party services, advertising networks, or analytics tools. It does not contain ads, in-app purchases, or any form of monetization.

4. Permissions
The App does not require any special permissions to access your device's features or data. It operates entirely within the scope of its intended functionality.

5. Data Deletion
Since all data is stored locally on your device, you can delete any information entered into the App at any time by clearing the App's data or uninstalling the App.

6. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. If we make any changes, we will notify you by updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your information.

7. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or the App, please contact us at yetanothergamedev2@gmail.com.

Summary:
Tabletop Tool is a simple tool for tracking health and items in tabletop games. It does not collect, store, or share any user data. All information entered into the App remains on your device and is not accessible to anyone else.